Model View Controller (MVC)
	- A way to architect software / Design Pattern
	- "Model" examples:
		- Data
		- Files
		- CSV / text
		- Business Logic
		- Back-end
	- "View" examples
		- User Interface
			- GUI
			- Text
		- Presents data visually
		- Front-end
		- i.e. JavaFX
	- "Controller"
		- Mechanism to take input from view and produce output from the model
		- Only one controller
		- Singleton
			- Constructor can make at most one object/controller
			- Ensures only one object will ever be made from a class
				- i.e. "static"
			- Make private constructor
			- Method named "getInstance"
				- returns reference to static instance
			- Google gang of 4